title: Drawing, Maiden Chased by a Satyr
description: Two figures depicted in outline. At left, a man with some traits of a satyr (long curling beard) or devil (curled tail and pointed genitalia) chases a nude woman at right, grabbing her rear end. title: Sidewall (France)
description: Diaper or trellis style design with stylized floral motif set within each lozenge. The background of each lozenge shades from light blue at the top to deeper blue at the bottom.

title: Frieze (USA)
description: The central motif is the Renaissance castle set high upon a hilltop, with a wide road drawn in a strong perspective, leading the viewer up into the castle. A horse-drawn wagon and guard appear on the road. The tops of the castle towers are cut off, making the castle feel more imposing. The surrounding country side is dotted with hills, trees and little cottages. Block-printed on paper embossed to resemble leather.
